HEADWORD: Platinocyanic
<hw>Plat`i*no*cy*an"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, derived from, or designating, an
acid compound of platinous cyanide and hydrocyanic acid. It is obtained
as a cinnaber-red crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Platinocyanide</ent>⟦br⟧
